cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper is about addressing presentation bias in search engines, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also proposes a new estimator, which involves machine learning techniques, so it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of historic feedback logs, which could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of presentation bias on user experience, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
